Certainly! Here is the code for the class `Solution` as seen in the image:

```java
class Solution {
    public TreeNode searchBST(TreeNode root, int val) {
        if (root == null) return null;
        if (root.val == val) return root;

        if (val < root.val) {
            return searchBST(root.left, val);
        } else {
            return searchBST(root.right, val);
        }
    }
}
```

This method performs a search in a Binary Search Tree (BST) to find a node with a specific value. If it finds the node, it returns it; otherwise, it returns `null`.
